rule.Name: AvoidUncalledPrivateCodeRule
rule.problem: This private or internal (assembly-level) member does not have callers in the assembly, is not invoked by the common language runtime, and is not invoked by a delegate.
rule.solution: Remove the unused code or add code to call it.

rule.Name: AvoidUninstantiatedInternalClassesRule
rule.problem: The internal type is not instantiated by code within the assembly.
rule.solution: Remove the type or add the code that uses it. If the type contains only static methods then either add the static modifier to the type or add the private construtor to the type to prevent the compiler from emitting a default public instance constructor.

rule.Name: AvoidUnsealedUninheritedInternalTypeRule
rule.problem: Due to performance issues, types which are not visible outside of the assembly and which have no derived types should be sealed.
rule.solution: You should seal this type, unless you plan to inherit from this type in the near-future.

rule.Name: CheckParametersNullityInVisibleMethodsRule
rule.problem: A visible method does not check its parameter(s) for null values.
rule.solution: Since the caller is unknown you should always verify all of your parameters to protect yourself.

rule.Name: ConsiderUsingStaticTypeRule
rule.problem: This type contains only static fields and methods and should be static.
rule.solution: Change this type into a static (or sealed for 1.x) type gain clarity and better error reporting.

rule.Name: DoNotSwallowErrorsCatchingNonSpecificExceptionsRule
rule.problem: This method catches a very general exception without rethrowing it. This is not safe to do in general and may mask problems that the caller should be made aware of.
rule.solution: Rethrow the original exception (which will preserve the stacktrace of the original error) or catch a more specific exception type.

rule.Name: MainShouldNotBePublicRule
rule.problem: The entry point (Main) of this assembly is visible to the outside world (ref: C# Programming Guide).
rule.solution: Reduce the visibility of the method or type if your language allows it. It may not be possible in some language, like VB.NET).

rule.Name: MarkAssemblyWithCLSCompliantRule
rule.problem: This assembly is not decorated with the [CLSCompliant] attribute.
rule.solution: Add this attribute to ease the use (or non-use) of your assembly by CLS consumers.

rule.Name: MarkAssemblyWithComVisibleRule
rule.problem: This assembly is not decorated with the [ComVisible] attribute.
rule.solution: Add this attribute to ease the use (or non-use) of your assembly by COM consumers.

rule.Name: PreferTryParseRule
rule.problem: Using a Parse method force you to catch multiple exceptions.
rule.solution: Use the existing TryParse alternative method.

rule.Name: UseStringEmptyRule
rule.problem: The method uses literal "" instead of String.Empty.
rule.solution: Replace the empty string literal with String.Empty.
